headlines.description: — Bogdan Bogdanovic scored 32 points on a career-high eight 3-pointers and the Atlanta Hawks battled back from a 10-point fourth quarter deficit to beat the Charlotte Hornets 105-101 Sunday without Trae Young.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bogdanovic scores 32 as Hawks beat Hornets 105-101

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum and Jaylen Brown fueled an amazing 31-3 run that helped the Boston Celtics put the skids on the NBA’s hottest team with a 105-87 win over the Denver Nuggets on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boston bullies: Celtics' 31-3 run ends Nuggets' win streak

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 38 points and Brandon Ingram had 27 points and eight assists in rallying the New Orleans Pelicans to a 116-109 victory over the injury-plagued Cleveland Cavaliers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson scores 38, Pelicans rally past Cavaliers 116-109

headlines.description: — Khris Middleton scored 21 points, Bobby Portis added 16 points, including four 3-pointers, and 10 rebounds off the bench and the Milwaukee Bucks defeated the Orlando Magic 124-87 on Sunday night to end a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Middleton, Portis lead Bucks past slumping Magic 124-87

events.name: Toronto Raptors at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 26 points and the New York Knicks recovered after blowing an 18-point lead to beat the Toronto Raptors 102-96 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks recover after blown lead to beat Raptors 102-96

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan hit the tiebreaking jumper with 0.5 seconds left, giving him 27 of his 33 points in the second half and lifting the San Antonio Spurs to a 119-117 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan ends Spurs' skid with late shot to beat Mavs 119-117

headlines.description: — Caris LeVert scored 34 points, Malcolm Brogdon and Donantas Sabonis fell just short of triple-doubles and the Indiana Pacers held on for a 132-125 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers hang on to beat Grizzlies behind LeVert, Brogdon

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 27 points and 12 rebounds, D’Angelo Russell scored 27 and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Chicago Bulls 121-117 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Russell push Wolves to 121-117 win against Bulls

headlines.description: — Marcus Morris Sr. scored a season-high 33 points, Paul George added 32 and the Los Angeles Clippers capped a nine-game homestand with a 131-124 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morris scores season-high 33 as Clippers win 5th straight

events.name: Miami Heat at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo scored 22 points and Jimmy Butler added 20 to lead the Miami Heat to a 107—98 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo has 22 points, Heat down Blazers 107-98
